&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Choose Well – Choose WWL&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you ready for a new challenge? Do you want to make a difference?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; Two Band 6 Acute Pain Sister roles have become available at Wrightington, Wigan and Leigh Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking a highly motivated nurse who has a desire to work and develop their skills within the Acute Pain Service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role will require you to work across all areas in the Trust which includes those that are designed as positive, asymptomatic and negative COVID wards. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Candidates will be required to present original certificates for qualifications at interview stage.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For overseas candidates wishing to apply for the job role and require immigration sponsorship, you can self-assess the likelihood of obtaining a CoS for the post on the GOV.UK website.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLisa JeffersonJob titleAcute Pain LeadEmail addresslisa.jefferson@wwl.nhs.ukTelephone number01942 822365Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like further information on this role please contact Lisa Jefferson on the above contact details&lt;/p&gt;
